Let me drink a little bit once more! 
I was not going back tonight, never thought of going back!
You said, who could have waited in that room for me?
Oh yes! From now there would be nobody anymore!
Please do not sing that song!
Because that would caused me to think of that heartless man who broke up with me, ah!
Once drinking, tears would yet forced out the rim of eyes,
Please excused me, the way I was,
The external Winter rain continued to drizzle non-stop,
As if drenching my heart,
Was not without an umbrella, just thought of not going back!
Just thought of drinking excessively till intoxicated, so as to forget about that ungrateful man, ah!

That heartless man who had abandoned me,
Even regret now, would be of no avail,
At this night of passionate love, was difficult to dismiss from one's mind,
A woman drinking alone, was unable to bear lonely emptiness,
I was not drunk, did not cry either,
My eyes was only pricked by misty smoke of cigarettes,
Got drunk! I could go home myself,
Please do not  worry for me, in such a way!
To forget about that ungrateful man, ah!
